wolf /wʊlf/

(wolfing,wolfed,wolfs,wolves) 

1. N-COUNT A wolf is a wild animal that looks like a large dog. 狼 

2. V-T If someone wolfs their food, they eat it all very quickly and greedily. 狼吞虎咽 [非正式] 

例： Hotels were full of rich people wolfing expensive meals. 酒店满是狼吞虎咽昂贵饭菜的有钱人。 

3. PHRASAL VERB Wolf down means the same as . 狼吞虎咽 

例： He wolfed down the rest of the biscuit and cheese. 他狼吞虎咽地吃下了剩余的饼干和奶酪。

